-- =============================================================================
-- V143 — whole-schema data_category catalog
--
-- Every governance audit so far (V136 row_version, V137 audit columns) only
-- ever scoped itself to dbo.master_data_table_registry — the ~104 tables
-- reachable through the generic Tier 2 CRUD grid. That's why both audits
-- kept missing real gaps on dedicated (non-Tier2) tables: gl_account (fixed
-- this session, V142) and storage_facility (found the same session) both
-- have real, user-facing CRUD via their own dedicated controllers, but
-- neither was ever in the registry, so neither was ever checked.
--
-- This migration doesn't fix those gaps yet — it builds the catalog needed
-- to find ALL of them reliably, going forward, instead of re-deriving the
-- list ad hoc each time (as this session just did by hand):
--
--   1. Adds `data_category` to master_data_table_registry, classifying every
--      table in dbo into one of four tiers (standard MDM terminology):
--        MASTER_CONFIG  — closed vocabulary, SYSTEM/migration-only, no GUI
--                          CRUD at all (e.g. commodity_instrument_type_config)
--        MASTER_DATA    — core business entities users maintain via GUI,
--                          whether through the generic Tier 2 grid or a
--                          dedicated Tier 1 controller (e.g. gl_account,
--                          storage_facility, legal_entity)
--        TRANSACTIONAL  — business events (trades, nominations, deliveries,
--                          amendments, margin calls) — high volume, records
--                          something that happened rather than a reference fact
--        DERIVED        — computed/append-only/log/junction tables with no
--                          independent identity to protect (temporal
--                          _history shadow tables, snapshots, staging logs,
--                          pure many-to-many junctions, flyway_schema_history)
--      All 104 existing registry rows default to MASTER_DATA (correct — every
--      one of them is already Tier2-generic-CRUD-editable).
--
--   2. Backfills a catalog-only row for every one of the 186 tables that
--      were previously invisible to the registry entirely — classified via
--      a first-pass, code-derived heuristic (real @PostMapping/@PutMapping
--      presence in the entity's own dedicated controller + naming
--      convention for event/junction/history-shaped tables), not a
--      table-by-table manual review. `is_enabled=0` on every one of these
--      186 rows — they must NOT appear on the Tier2HomePage Static Data
--      landing page (it already filters on isEnabled) or be treated as
--      generic-CRUD-capable; they exist purely so `data_category`-based
--      governance queries have something to scan. `allow_create/edit/
--      delete/excel_upload` all 0 for the same reason — these flags are
--      meaningless for a non-Tier2 table and must never be read as "this
--      table supports generic CRUD."
--
-- Next step (tracked separately, not this migration): query
-- `WHERE data_category = 'MASTER_DATA' AND is_enabled = 0` cross-referenced
-- against sys.columns for the governance-column gap, and fix only the
-- confirmed real gaps (storage_facility first) — not the derived/
-- transactional/junction tables mixed into the raw 186-table sweep, most of
-- which legitimately don't need created_by/updated_by at all.
-- =============================================================================

ALTER TABLE dbo.master_data_table_registry ADD
    data_category VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'MASTER_DATA'
        CONSTRAINT ck_registry_data_category CHECK (data_category IN ('MASTER_CONFIG','MASTER_DATA','TRANSACTIONAL','DERIVED'));
GO


GO

